11/11/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian war crimes prosecutors announced on Friday (November 9th) that they have charged a Bosnian national with war crimes committed during the 1992-1995 conflict. Ilija Jurisic, 64, is accused of ordering an attack on a former Yugoslav National Army convoy in May 1992, which claimed the lives of 92 soldiers and left 33 wounded. Jurisic was arrested at Belgrade Airport last May. (AFP, Tanjug - 09/11/07; MIA, B92, Beta - 10/11/07)
